<TITLE> Jamuna Park plea hearing Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 21 (bdnews24.com)--The High Court has deferred to Sunday the hearing of a petition against a Rajuk order for demolishing unapproved portions of Jamuna Future Park. A bench of Justice AHM Shamsuddin Chowdhury and Justice Md Borhanuddin on Thursday gave the prosecution more time after additional attorney general Murad Reza filed an appeal. The city's development authority Rajdhani Unnayan Kortripakkho on Sunday gave the authorities seven days to knock down the illegal installations of the Park, a project of Jamuna Group. Rajuk official Shaqur Rahman had told bdnews24.com that Park had built beyond the approved six floors. Nurul Islam, chief of Jamuna Future Park and owner of the daily Jugantar newspaper, challenged the Rajuk order in court. The much-vaunted Future Park is being constructed on 10 acres of land in the capital's Bashundhara area. Jamuna has been claiming that it would be the largest shopping mall in South Asia. b
